            <li>The next important step is to choose the right Wheel size: <strong>26"</strong>,<strong>27,5"</strong>,<strong>29"</strong>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Don’t obsess about weight</strong>: Check the reviews of the forks and shocks (on full susspension) on the bike you’re looking at, and use the manufacturer’s site to get the exact models!
            </li>
            <li><strong>Choose suspension quality, not quantity</strong>: Weight is important, but off-road, strength is marginally more important!
            </li>
            <li><strong>Keep some budget back</strong>: Often you need some parts to replace the broken ones or bald tyres. Moreover, there are a lot of necessary part you need like a fidlock bottle
            </li>
